---
// My Approach to Code & Tech
---

<section class="py-20 px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 bg-text-secondary/30">
  <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
    <div class="text-center mb-16">
      <p class="uppercase text-sm tracking-widest text-gray-500 font-medium mb-4">Philosophy</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-bold text-black mb-6">
        My Approach to <span class="text-yellow-400">Code</span>
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 max-w-2xl mx-auto leading-relaxed">
        How I think about technology, problem-solving, and building things that matter.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-12">
      
      <!-- Code Philosophy -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div>
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">Code is Communication</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
           I write code like I’m handing it to my future self. Clear. Simple. No puzzles. Whether I’m building solo or on a team, the goal is the same: make things understandable. Tech should enable not complicate.
          </p>
          
        </div>
        <div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-6 border-l-4 border-yellow-400">
          <div class="mb-4">
            <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-yellow-400 mb-2" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M9 12h6m-6 4h6m2 5H7a2 2 0 01-2-2V5a2 2 0 012-2h5.586a1 1 0 01.707.293l5.414 5.414a1 1 0 01.293.707V19a2 2 0 01-2 2z"/>
            </svg>
          </div>
          <blockquote class="text-gray-800 italic leading-relaxed">
            "Any fool can write code that a computer can understand. Good programmers write code that humans can understand."
          </blockquote>
          <cite class="text-gray-600 text-sm mt-2 block">— Martin Fowler</cite>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Problem Solving -->
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
        <div class="order-2 md:order-1 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-4">How I Solve Problems</h4>
          <div class="space-y-3">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <div>
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">Start with the human. Who needs this? Why now? Then I break the problem into smaller ones and build from there. I’d rather ship something useful today than wait for perfect.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="order-1 md:order-2">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-4">People-First Development</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed mb-4">
            I build things for people, not just specs. If the app makes someone’s day smoother or a business run cleaner, I’ve done my job. Tech’s just the vehicle the destination is usefulness.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed">
            I treat every project like it’s mine  whether I’m freelancing, studying, or working on a team. I care about how things are built, but I care even more about whether they ship and work in the real world.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Tech Philosophy -->
      <div class="text-center">
        <div class="bg-gradient-to-r from-gray-50 to-yellow-50 rounded-2xl p-8">
          <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-bold text-black mb-6">How I See Technology</h3>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8 text-left">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-3">Tools, Not Religions</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
             I aim to be tool-agnostic. Frameworks come and go, but fundamentals stick. If you understand how the web works, you can adapt to anything whether it’s React, Astro, or whatever shows up next year.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-3">Boring is Beautiful</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
               I love experimenting but when it’s time to ship, I stick to what works. Proven tech wins over clever hacks. I’d rather build something stable and maintainable than chase the next hype cycle. If boring gets us to production, boring is beautiful.
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-semibold text-black mb-3">Always Learning</h4>
              <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">
                Tech moves fast, but I don’t panic. I stay curious, and learn on purpose. I don’t memorize API docs I learn how systems work. That’s what lets me adapt when the landscape shifts. I’m not here to master tools. I’m here to master problem-solving
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>